# Host-specific dashcam NFS coordinates for `task k8s:<env>:dashcam-pv`.
#
# Copy to `dashcam-nfs.local.env` (gitignored) and fill in your NAS export.
# The task sources these and synths the cluster-scoped dashcam PersistentVolume
# with them, applying it OUTSIDE Argo (the committed dist/ carries placeholders,
# so no host specifics live in git). prod uses NFS_PATH (the airing export); one
# file serves both, the per-env PV name differs (config.py).
#
# Quote the values — the task sources this file with sh, so paths with spaces or
# an apostrophe (e.g. a NAS share like "Dana's Photos") need double quotes.
NFS_SERVER="<NFS server address>"
NFS_PATH="<export path>"

# Optional: point STAGE at a different export than prod. Unset → stage uses
# NFS_PATH (same as prod). Set it to stream the regenerated _opt corpus on stage
# (e.g. the ADanaLife share's _opt/clips). After changing it, recreate the stage
# PV+PVC (NFS path is immutable on a bound PV) — see `task k8s:stage:dashcam-pv`.
# STAGE_NFS_PATH="<regenerated _opt clips export>"
